Thank you for the advice, Woody.

03:59.300 --> 04:01.300
    Now may I have a scotch     
     on the rocks, please?      

04:01.300 --> 04:02.900
                    Okeydoke!   

04:03.000 --> 04:06.000
            That'll be around   
                    1,200 bucks.

04:07.400 --> 04:09.500
     Oh, Frasier, you know,     
 it's a good thing you're here  

04:09.500 --> 04:11.100
                because we gotta
            think of some way   

04:11.200 --> 04:13.200
          to get that crazy lady
              out of the office.

04:13.200 --> 04:14.600
             It's been two days.

04:14.700 --> 04:16.500
      Well, I realize that      
 you're concerned about Rebecca 

04:16.600 --> 04:18.000
  and that you all look to me   

04:18.000 --> 04:19.800
         as the solver          
of all problems personal,       

04:19.800 --> 04:21.600
    but, in this case,          
  I have to throw up my hands.  

04:21.700 --> 04:23.500
    I mean, there's a limit     
     to what even I can do.     

04:23.600 --> 04:25.100
                And we also know
                    how you pout

04:25.200 --> 04:26.800
          when we don't ask you.

04:28.800 --> 04:30.700
         Well... fine.          

04:30.800 --> 04:32.700
    Maybe I'll just go home.    

04:34.700 --> 04:36.300
             Okay!              

04:36.300 --> 04:38.300
  I've got the tool box here.   

04:38.300 --> 04:41.300
I'm gonna get Rebecca out       
of that office right now.       

04:42.800 --> 04:44.900
            Rebecca!            

04:45.000 --> 04:47.700
  I've got a screwdriver here!  

04:47.800 --> 04:49.800
I'm gonna take that doorknob off

04:49.800 --> 04:52.800
  and I'm gonna open the door   
             here.              

04:54.200 --> 04:57.800
 Rebecca, I got a Phillips head 
          by mistake,           

