     Rebecca, I don't have      
          a flathead,           

05:13.000 --> 05:16.000
    but I have one of those     
          putty things          

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
    and I'm gonna put it...     

05:18.000 --> 05:20.300
             Damn!              

05:20.400 --> 05:24.000
Okay, Rebecca, I just punctured 
my thumb with that, uh...       

05:24.000 --> 05:27.200
  putty thing and I'm gonna go  
      get a tetanus shot,       

05:27.300 --> 05:29.200
          then I'm...           

05:29.300 --> 05:31.200
coming back here                
and taking that doorknob off.   

05:31.300 --> 05:33.200
              Here's a Band-Aid.

05:33.300 --> 05:35.100
Hey, hey, guys!                 
Rebecca!                        

05:35.200 --> 05:36.700
Hey!                            
    Rebecca's out.              
                        REBECCA:
                         No, no.

05:36.800 --> 05:38.000
              Don't say Rebecca.

05:38.000 --> 05:39.500
                Don't call me   
                        Rebecca.

05:39.600 --> 05:42.500
            Rebecca doesn't live
                here anymore.   

05:42.600 --> 05:45.500
                Rebecca died two
                    days ago.   

05:45.600 --> 05:47.600
Oh! So that's                   
what that is.                   

05:47.700 --> 05:50.500
    Whoof!                      

05:50.500 --> 05:51.800
I'm telling you,                

05:51.900 --> 05:54.900
a woman should never            
sweat in taffeta.               

05:56.800 --> 05:58.500
              Have a seat.      
                Come on.        

05:58.600 --> 06:00.700
                      Thank you.

06:00.700 --> 06:02.300
                         Wow.   

06:02.400 --> 06:04.100
                I've never sat  
                 here before.   

06:06.100 --> 06:08.200
              Here I am, sitting
                  on this stool,

06:08.300 --> 06:10.700
                 knowing my life
                      is a mess.

06:10.800 --> 06:12.900
        I have no future, and...

06:13.000 --> 06:15.700
                 I'm a totally  
            hopeless failure.   

06:15.800 --> 06:17.700
  Yeah. Try it                  
  with beer nuts.               

06:21.300 --> 06:22.900
             It is all my fault.

06:22.900 --> 06:24.600
                I mean, I got   
                 what I deserve.

06:24.700 --> 06:25.800
              And now I'm alone.

06:25.800 --> 06:28.200
             I... I have nothing
                 and I'm just a,

06:28.200 --> 06:30.800
            you know, worthless,
                 shallow person.

06:30.900 --> 06:33.800
I'm telling you,                
try it with the beer nuts.      

06:35.900 --> 06:38.300
        Rebecca...              

06:38.400 --> 06:41.100
  I realize you haven't sought  
  my professional advice, but   

06:41.200 --> 06:43.200
I think it's time               
to get some perspective,        

06:43.300 --> 06:44.600
    take a look at yourself.    

06:44.700 --> 06:48.000
 Splash some water on your face 
     and get a fresh start.     

06:48.000 --> 06:49.400
        I'd like to, Frasier,   

06:49.500 --> 06:52.100
         but I seem to have lost
            the will to move.   

06:52.200 --> 06:55.100
         I just want to sit here
        for the rest of my life.

06:55.200 --> 06:57.400
          Geez, maybe           
        it's the stool.         

07:03.300 --> 07:05.200
                        Come on,
                      Miss Howe.

07:05.300 --> 07:07.300
                Woody...        

07:07.400 --> 07:10.000
         have you ever          
      had your whole life       

07:10.000 --> 07:12.000
              cave in on you    
             all of a sudden?   

07:12.000 --> 07:14.300
  No, but I have had            
  a cave cave in on me          

07:14.400 --> 07:16.700
    all of a sudden.            

07:16.700 --> 07:19.100
You know, at the risk           
of sounding insensitive,        

07:19.200 --> 07:22.100
I'm... I'm glad she's           
getting out of here.            

07:22.200 --> 07:24.300
Her walking around              
in that wedding dress           

07:24.300 --> 07:26.800
was just a tad too              
"Miss Havisham" for me.         

07:28.100 --> 07:30.000
                        Who?    
Miss Havisham.                  

07:30.000 --> 07:31.600
Famous character                
from Charles Dickens'           

07:31.700 --> 07:33.300
 <i>Great Expectations.</i>            

07:33.400 --> 07:34.600
Spends the entire novel         

07:34.600 --> 07:35.900
walking around                  
in her wedding dress.           

07:36.000 --> 07:37.900
                What?!          
                            Yes.

07:38.000 --> 07:39.800
Well, surely you know it.       

07:39.800 --> 07:41.400
    It's <i>Great Expectations.</i>    

07:41.500 --> 07:43.300
      Pip? Miss Havisham?       

07:43.300 --> 07:44.800
            Magwich?            

07:44.900 --> 07:48.200
And, uh... and four...          

07:48.200 --> 07:49.300
pizza-loving turtles            

07:49.400 --> 07:51.600
who practice martial            
arts in the sewer.              

07:53.100 --> 07:56.200
        Oh, cowabunga, dudes!   

07:56.200 --> 07:57.500
                          CLIFF:
                    You know,   

07:57.500 --> 07:59.000
there's a lot of people         
    don't realize               

07:59.100 --> 08:01.000
      that that was             
a comic book first.             

